Minimalistic style: A stark white canvas featuring a single descending staircase made of translucent blue geometric blocks, casting soft shadows as it steps down from the upper left to the lower right corner. Scattered across several steps are small crimson cubes that interrupt the clean descent, representing obstacles and scope changes. The staircase appears to be dissolving into pixels at its lowest point, suggesting progress toward completion. The composition uses negative space dramatically, with the geometric forms floating against the pure white background. Subtle grid lines in very light gray suggest measurement and tracking. The overall mood is clean, analytical, and forward-moving, evoking the satisfaction of watching work diminish over time while honestly acknowledging the disruptions along the way.
